The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Friday, March 12, 2004  Calcutta Column

	Exchanging soiled and mutilated currency is a time-consuming process at the Reserve Bank of India (RBI)s office at Dalhousie. A few private banks that are authorised to exchange such notes refuse to do so on one pretext or the other. The RBI should see to it that consumers are not harassed this way. 
	Rabindranath Kar, Sankar Ghosh Lane. 
	I had applied to the CESC for an electricity connection at 58-D, NS Road in August 2002. But I have not been obliged despite innumerable requests and even offers to deposit the security money on demand. The commercial manager assured me that an inspector would visit the premises but no one has turned up to date. 
	Chand Mal Baid, Netaji Subhas Road. 
	With the advent of summer, mosquitoes have become a menace in Salt Lake. Its exam time but students are unable to study in peace. The Bidhannagar Municipality should take action. 
	Diptimoy Ghosh, Salt Lake. 

